8:
There's no way I can go out in this!
I'm a huge introvert, this would be
way out of character for me!
12:
Hmm... I don't think anyone will
recognize you! You really should
give it a try—it looks great on you!
22:
Erm? Y-you're not pulling my leg, are
you? Hehe...
26:
Wait—YOU ARE, AREN'T YOU?! Why do
I have to go out in this outfit?!
31:
It was a request, of course! You'll be
passing out presents to all of the
kids and... Wait, didn't we go over
this last week?
39:
That does sound familiar... But I was
busy pouring my heart and soul into
my manuscript! I probably wasn't
even paying attention to you!
44:
A promise is a promise! Anyway, we
need to get going! Those presents
aren't going to hand themselves
out! Let's go!
49:
Eek?! Wait just a minute! Give me at
least some time to prepare!
53:
H-happy holidays! Come get your
presents... Hehehehe...
57:
Erm... Meryll, could you try to act
more cheery? And maybe lose the
creepy laugh? You'll scare the kids.
62:
No way! That's just who I am!
Ugh, this "shy girl has to learn to be
more open" trope is so overused!
67:
What exactly does she mean by
that? What is a "trope"?
72:
That's a rabbit hole you don't want
to go down, Light. Anyway, her Santa
impression could really use some
work, don't you think?
85:
And for you... Since you were such a
good boy... you get a picture book!
89:
Wait, is this the newest entry in the
"Wandering Knight" series?! I LOVED
this one!
92:
A tale about a knight, huh? Now that
sounds intriguing.
98:
You've read it too?! The tension
between the knight and dragon's
fiery love and their need to kill each
other had me SHAKING!
101:
I don't like that. I wanted something
else.
104:
Oh no, really? Sorry about that, looks
like there was a mistake...
108:
Erm, how about this. Could you tell
me what you wanted?
112:
The knight loses in that one! So I
want a different one!
118:
Is it one of those endings that's a
real downer?
123:
Not... exactly? It kind of leaves off on
a cliffhanger. But there's a lot of
foreshadowing suggesting the
knight will be resurrected, and—
126:
But I asked Santa to make the knight
WIN! It's not fair!
130: Hmm, let's see what we can do...
133:
How about this? Our daring knight
comes back to life—and realizes he
was in love with the dragon all along!
136:
Wow! The knight is back! Are you an
author too, Santa?
139:
A-absolutely not! I-I'm just a stickler
for making fans' fantasies a reality!
142:
Ooh, then after that... The knight
should become friends with the
adventurer he met in the beginning!
145:
Now THAT'S a plot development! He
could be all cocky at the start, like
"Hmph, it's not like I wanted to save
you or anything," but then he'll start
to open up!
150:
Which sets up a love triang—I mean,
rivalry with the squire! "Sir, surely I
am the only companion you need
on this journey..."
153:
Oh my gosh! I need to stop myself
before this scene gets any juicier!
159:
The pleasure is mine! You have a
very bright future as a writer ahead
of you, young man!
163:
Me next, Santa! Can you write a new
chapter of "Sailor Sun" for me?
Please?
172:
W-wait just a minute there!
P-please form a line! A line!
176: The end of the line starts here!
183: Light... How long is this going to last?
187:
It should only be a while longer! The
line is beginning to thin out.
Somewhat.
192:
What?! We should definitely be done
by now! We're getting into overtime
territory!
202:
BWAAAH! What kind of a shady
operation are you running here?!
